This repository contains tools and resources for the computational processing of the Nheengatu language. Its main component is GrammYEP, a multilingual computational grammar comprising equivalent Nheengatu, English and Portuguese modules. GrammYEP enables automatic translation between these three langauges. It also comprises different test sets and a multilingual treebank with semantic representations.

For more details, see

ALENCAR, Leonel Figueiredo de. Uma gram√°tica computacional de um fragmento do nheengatu. Revista de Estudos da Linguagem, Belo Horizonte, v. 29, p. 1717-1777, 2021. ISSN 2237-2083. 
Available at http://www.periodicos.letras.ufmg.br/index.php/relin/article/view/17313 
DOI http://dx.doi.org/10.17851/2237-2083.29.3.1717-1777

If you use this repository in your research, please cite this paper.


